<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringmap">StringMap</a> - This is an unconventional map that is specialized for handling keys that are &quot;strings&quot;, which are basically ranges of bytes.

This does some funky memory allocation and hashing things to make it extremely efficient, storing the string data <em>after</em> the value in the map.

Definition at line 126 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/adt/stringmap-h">StringMap.h</a>.

### try&#95;emplace() {#acef94957604524790af3fbcb3cebc050}

  labels = {["inline"]}>
Emplace a new element for the specified key into the map if the key isn&#39;t already in the map.

The bool component of the returned pair is true if and only if the insertion takes place, and the iterator component of the pair points to the element with key equivalent to the key of the pair.
